<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910426-0122</DOCNO><DOCID>910426-0122.</DOCID><HL>   Raychem Corp. Posts   Loss of $1.6 Million   For Its Third Quarter</HL><DATE>04/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   RYC</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)</RE><LP>   MENLO PARK, Calif. -- Raychem Corp. said it posted a lossof $1.6 million, or four cents a share, for the third quarterended March 31.   A year earlier, the company had a loss of $108 million, or$3.01 a share, reflecting a one-time charge of $90 million.Sales rose 10% to $322 million from $292 million.</LP><TEXT>   In late March, the company said it expected soft sales andprofits, with recessionary pressures likely to cause itselectronics, telecommunications, and industrial segments tofall short of expecations. Before that announcement, analystsforecast earnings of 22 cents a share.   Raychem has been hurt by a declines in defense spendingand losses in Raynet, a unit that is developing a fiberoptics technology. That unit had a pretax loss of $17million, equal to last year's third quarter, the companysaid.   &quot;Except for moderately disappointing sales, we'recomfortable with all the internal ratios,&quot; said Raymond J.Sims, the company's treasurer. &quot;No part of the business issuffering unduly, but across all segments, sales are soft,&quot;he said.   With gross margins up 2% to 48% from 46% a year ago, Mr.Sims said a small sales increase would fuel a rapid recoveryto earnings. Shipments rose 9% in all segments of thebusiness operations to $319 million from $291 million a yearago.   In the first nine months, net income was $2.8 million, oreight cents a share, against a net loss, reflecting the $90million charge, of $98 million, or $2.75 a share, a yearearlier.   In composite trading yesterday on the New York StockExchange, the stock fell 62.5 cents to close at $25.</TEXT></DOC>